<h3>Strategy Tips</h3>
<div class="tip-card">💡 <strong>Preparing for the Underground:</strong>
<ul style="margin:4px 0 0 0">
  <li>Minimum <strong>full iron armor and weapon</strong> — Hardstone/Ancient Metal for deeper levels</li>
  <li>Bring at least <strong>64 torches</strong> and <strong>Flint and Steel</strong></li>
  <li>Always mark your return path (torches always on the left → on the right coming back)</li>
  <li>Build a <strong>Return Portal</strong> before going too deep (Obsidian frame underground → returns to overworld)</li>
  <li><strong>Ancient Metal sword</strong> is essential for Phase Spiders — no other weapon works!</li>
  <li>Bring potions (Regeneration, Night Vision) if available</li>
</ul></div>
<div class="tip-card">⚔️ <strong>Best Underground weapon:</strong> <strong>High-Carbon Steel War Hammer + Undead Slayer V</strong> one-shots skeletons and undead. Cheap, durable, also hits Earth Elementals (Stone Golems).</div>
<div class="tip-card">💎 <strong>Mithril sources:</strong> The more solidly supported sources here are <strong>mithril ore itself</strong> and the <strong>underground Pillager camp mechanism</strong>. There are community reports about mithril in spawner-room loot, but I am not treating that as confirmed fact here.</div>

<h3>Pillager Camp — Hidden Treasure</h3>
<div class="warning-box">⚔️ <strong>v0.9.0 Pillager camp difficulty warning!</strong> The camp interior is <strong>drastically harder</strong> in v0.9.0:
<ul style="margin:6px 0 0 0">
  <li><strong>10+ Vindicator spawners</strong> inside the building — one every 2-3 steps</li>
  <li>Vindicators <strong>can break blocks</strong> (they'll dig to reach you!)</li>
  <li>Faster spawn rate than before</li>
  <li>Rewards reduced: <strong>Carbon Crystal removed</strong> from loot, replaced with less valuable minerals</li>
</ul>
<strong>Do not enter unprepared</strong> — enchanted golden apple and at least Hardstone/Ancient Metal gear is required!</div>
<div class="tip-card">⚙️ <strong>Pillager camp underground mechanism:</strong> In the underground Pillager camp, <strong>place anvils around the camp + activate a lever in the center</strong> → this opens an underground chamber containing <strong>Adamantium, Mithril, and Redstone blocks</strong>. This is one of the main mithril sources in the game!</div>

<h3>Underground → Nether Gateway</h3>
<p>In the deepest level of the Underground, at the <strong>bedrock layer</strong>, you'll find the <strong>Mantle</strong> — the gateway to the Nether dimension. Build a portal on the magma layer to reach the Nether.</p>
<div class="info-box">🔥 <strong>On Hard Difficulty, there are 3 bedrock layers!</strong> Finding the Mantle may take longer.</div>


